05854nam a22006495i 9780292759077DE-B159720211129102213.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211129t20211977txu    fo  d z      eng d  a97802927590777 a10.7560/7753292doi  a(DE-B1597)586570  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  atxucUS-TX 7aREL0000002bisacsh00aSalvation in New England :bSelections from the Sermons of the First Preachers /ced. by Phyllis M. Jones, Nicholas R. Jones. 1aAustin : bUniversity of Texas Press, c[2021] 4c©1977  a1 online resource (212 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tIllustrations -- tPreface -- tIntroduction -- tThe Texts of the Sermons -- tSELECTION I The Gospel-Covenant -- tSELECTION II A Treatise of the Covenant of Grace -- tSELECTION III The Sound Believer -- tSELECTION IV The Soul's Vocation, Doctrine 3 -- tSELECTION V The Soul's Vocation, Doctrine 7 -- tSELECTION VI The Soul's Exaltation -- tSELECTION VII The Way of Life -- tSELECTION VIII The Parable of the Ten Virgins -- tSELECTION IX The Saint's Anchor-Hold -- tAppendix A Biographies of the Preachers -- tAppendix B Checklist of the Earliest Authoritative Editions of the Sermons and Sermon-Series of the Preachers -- tAppendix C Recommended Background Reading -- tNotes to the Introduction -- tNotes to The Texts of the Sermons -- tNotes to the Selections0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe sermon as crafted by the early New England preachers was the most prominent literary form of its day, yet the earliest Puritan texts have as a rule been available only in rare-book collections. This anthology of sermons of the first generation of preachers fills a serious gap in American literature. The preachers collected here, the most widely published of their time, were among the eighty or more who emigrated to Massachusetts Bay during the 1630s. They are John Cotton of Boston, Thomas Shepard of Cambridge, and Thomas Hooker of Hartford, the three foremost "lights of the western churches," and two eminent colleagues, Peter Bulkeley of Concord and John Davenport, first of New Haven and later of Boston. The selections are chosen to be representative of the lengthy works from which they are drawn, to reflect the major concerns and styles of the preachers' work as a whole, and to demonstrate the genre of the sermon as developed by the early American Puritans. Not only does this anthology represent an important contribution to literary history, but the sermons also illustrate a doctrine uniquely elaborated in this period—a consistent and emphatic narrative, mythlike in its repetition and heroics, of the progress of the soul from a state of nature to a state of salvation. This theme may be seen as a three-stage-development, although individual sermons may vary. These stages—preparation, vocation, and regeneration—determine the order of the selections. The editors' introductory material supplies a comprehensive and thorough discussion of the early New England sermons, concentrating on their role, history, structure, style, and subject matter. A separate essay on the texts of the sermons describes the relationship between the early printed versions and their form as delivered in the pulpit. The introduction preceding each selection presents original research on the historical circumstances of the preaching and publication of the work from which the sermon is drawn. The editors have also provided brief biographies of the preacfiers represented here, an annotated list of recommended background reading, and the most exhaustive checklist available of authoritative editions of the sermons of these five preachers. This book will be useful to colonial specialists as well as to students of early American literature, religion, and history. The texts are critically edited for readability, with modernized spelling and annotations of unfamiliar phrases and allusions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh1 aBulkeley, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCotton, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavenport, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHooker, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, Nicholas R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJones, Phyllis M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aShepard, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/77532940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292759077423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292759077/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK